2026-05-03 | Check if String is Rotation of Another

	Question
Return true if goal is a rotation of s.
	Key Insight
If goal is a rotation of s:
		it must be a substring of (s + s)  
Example:
		s = "abcde"  
		s+s = "abcdeabcde"  
		goal = "cdeab" → present inside  
	Approach
1.	If lengths differ → return false  
2.	Create string temp = s + s  
3.	Check if goal is substring of temp  
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool rotateString(string s, string goal) {
        if(s.size() != goal.size())
            return false;
        string temp = s + s;
        return temp.find(goal) != string::npos;
    }
};
	Key Insight
All rotations of s are contained in:
		s + s  
So we just need to check:
		is goal a substring of s+s  
This avoids simulating rotations explicitly.
